      <description>"J.W. ""Cotton"" Merchant worked with Gillis Long in the early 1960s when
            Long was a Congressman. Gillis Long (1923-1985) was representative for the 8th U.S.
            Congressional District of Louisiana in 1963-1965 and 1973-1985. He ran unsuccessfully
            for governor of Louisiana in 1964 and 1971."</description>
   </name>
